- Define a struct with a member of each of the types bool, char, int, long,
double and long double. Order the members so as to get the largest size of the
struct and the smallest size of the struct.

smallest size we get with this order:
struct little_struct {
	long double ld;
	double d;
	long l;
	int i;
	char c;
	bool b;
};

biggest size we get (because of alignment):
struct big_struct {
	char c;
	long double ld;
	bool b;
	double d;
	long l;
	int i;
};
